{
  "stem": "22047.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I'll talk about this a little later, associated with the Holocaust commemoration, where I met some of the people from the 45th Division who were-- were invited because of the liberation.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we got to this concentration camp, and we-- we didn't meet any resistance, and I didn't know why.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why didn't we get fired upon as we came toward the camp?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, it was because, as I said, the elements had gotten there before us and had killed all the-- the combatants.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And our-- my job-- I was informed by the battalion commander-- my job was to take my company into the camp and guard it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I felt rather strange with a-- a-- an order like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We're supposed to be liberating these-- the-- the prisoners of war that are in this camp, right?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we-- we broke down the-- the entrance to the camp and went in and could not believe what we saw-- thousands and thousands of people, emaciated, stacks of bodies who had recently been killed.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I'll tell you why that happened a few minutes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I-- I met a Belgian officer who had been captured a few months earlier.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he spoke good English.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I said, what is going on here?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I don't know quite what the emotions were, but revulsion, I guess, is one.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Stark shock is another.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "How could this be?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "How could so many people be in this condition?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because we had no concept of what a concentration camp was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I guess I should have known that it wasn't a POW camp because of the size of it, the walls around it, and the barbed wire, and the-- and the-- the towers, and all that.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
